 The huge amount of global deforestation is expected to occur in less than a dozen global hostpots .
Research by wildlife charity the WWF identified 11 ` deforestation fronts ' where 80 per cent of projected global forest losses by 2030 could occur .
By 2030 up to 170 million hectares acres - 80 million acres of forest - could be lost in just 11 hotspots , and eastern Australia .
The fronts are home to indigenous communities that depend them for indigenous species .